The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Konnagar emerge champions
                                                                                                                       7                                      Konnagar emerge champions
            A CORRESPONDENT                      
	Calcutta: Konnagar won the 52nd Winter National Bridge Championships at the Netaji Indoor Stadium in the newly introduced Ruia Silver for Teams. Of the 96 teams participating, Konnagar finished on top in the Swiss finals of 9 rounds with 176.31 VPs.         
	SAIL, ISP are the runners-up with 161.08 VPs. A.K. Upadhaya finished third. The winners and runners-up take home Rs 36,000 and Rs 18,000, respectively along with the trophies. All the 10 finalists get cash prizes.         
	In the Ruia Gold Teams, Sunil Machhar of Mumbai topped the Super Swiss of 6 rounds with 114.48 VPs. As per the format, they get to choose their opponents. And they have chosen their fellow citymates, Poddar Developers in the 54 Board knockout quarter final.         
	Formidables of Delhi finished second with 113.96 VPs and they have chosen Shree Cement as their opponents. MMRMC, who finished third, opted for India Blues and the 4th place qualifiers, Indian Railway B, get C.V. Rao as their opponents, to round off the last of the quarter finalists.         
	The big upset in the Ruia Gold was the elimination of both, last years winners and runners-up, Indian Railway A and Dhampur Sugar Mills, respectively. Also not making the grade was Team Jalan, winners of the recently held third Commonwealth Bridge Championships.         
	In the IMP Pairs that concluded Monday, D. Chakravarty amp; D. Mukherjee emerged as national champions followed by the runners UP, B P Dhibar-S Banerjee. In third place were S K Majhi-J L Singh. The winners get Rs 15,000, Rs 10,000 and Rs 6,000 respectively.                                                                                                                     
